II. Skills & Perks
Two-Handed (Master)
Galmar is one of the finest warriors in Skyrim.
Skullcrusher: Attacks ignore 2 DR.
Devastating Blow: Power Attacks deal +3 Damage.
Sweep: Spend 4 FP to hit all enemies in front.
Warmaster: Critical hits have a chance to Paralyze the target (stun them with pure force).
Heavy Armor (Master)
Tower of Strength: Immune to stagger/knockdown.
Reflect Blows: Once per adventure, reflect full melee damage back to attacker.
Smithing (Master)
Flavor: Galmar maintains his own gear and the gear of his elite guard. His weapons are sharper and his armor is tougher than anything the Empire can mass-produce.
Speech (Expert - Intimidation)
Battle Cry: As a Nord, he can use his Major Action to terrify enemies. Galmar's version affects all enemies within 30 feet.

III. Abilities & Techniques
Racial Ability: Nordic Frost Resistance
Takes -2 Damage from all Frost sources.
Unique Passive: Warlord's Presence
Galmar is a symbol of the Rebellion. As long as he is standing and conscious, all Stormcloak allies (and allied players) within 30 feet are Immune to Fear.
Master's Form: "The Bear's Verdict"
Style: Might (Two-Handed)
Description: Galmar raises his hammer and brings it down with the force of an executioner. This is not a combat move; it is a judgment. He intends to end the fight in a single stroke by shattering the enemy's body.
Cost: 4 FP + Major Action.
Roll: Might (TN 19).
Effect:
Massive Damage: The attack deals Weapon Damage + 6.
Armor Break: The attack ignores ALL Damage Reduction.
Concussion: On a hit, the target must make a Might Save or be Staggered (lose next turn).
Drawback: Galmar cannot move on the turn he uses this. He plants his feet and swings.



